{"type":"message","id":"4fb3a080","parentId":"57cacd69","timestamp":"2026-06-01T07:04:41.675Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Report: What Happened & Recovery\n\n**Root cause:** Git commit `fffec42` (\"chore: remove Aider, switch to direct edits for multi-file refactors\") committed on **May 30 at 21:43** replaced the full `tasks.json` with an empty `[]`. Whoever made that commit included the tasks file in the commit with zeroed-out contents — probably the file was emptied during the Aider cleanup work and got staged+committed inadvertently.\n\n**Timeline:**\n- May 30 21:39 — `tasks-archive.json` (33 done tasks) is created\n- May 30 21:43 — `tasks.json` gets wiped to `[]` and committed to git\n\n**Recovery:** ✅ **35 tasks restored** (32 done + 3 in-progress) by:\n1. Pulling the pre-wipe version from git (`fffec42^` parent) — 30 tasks\n2. Merging in 5 additional done tasks from `tasks-archive.json` that were completed after the git snapshot but before the wipe\n\n**The 3 in-progress tasks are back:**\n- \"Error Feed — behaviour review and fix.\" (lifesupport)\n- \"Task Completion — summary and visibility improvement.\" (archivist)\n- \"Agent Office Overall\" (monkey)\n\n**Recommendations:**\n- The tasks page should load correctly now — refresh and verify\n- Consider adding a pre-commit hook or guard that warns when `tasks.json` drops below a threshold (e.g., \"you're about to commit an empty tasks file with 0 entries — are you sure?\")\n- The `tasks-archive.json` pattern saved us — worth keeping as a rolling backup"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":106,"output":373,"cacheRead":31104,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":31583,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780297453546,"responseId":"gen-1780297453-gsgQ7WpQzzh9T0rDX6fI"}}
