{"type":"message","id":"0d7d291d","parentId":"8a1a0cda","timestamp":"2026-06-01T07:29:25.759Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"8e2de070-bac6-4de8-8267-b93496d977a2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Keep this file empty (or with only comments) to skip heartbeat API calls.\n\n# Add tasks below when you want the agent to check something periodically.\n\n## Task Pickup\n- Read `data/tasks.json`, find tasks with `status: \"backlog\"`\n- For each backlog task, spawn a sub-agent (or work directly if simple) to complete it\n- Move task to `in_progress` when starting, `done` when complete\n- Write completion summary before marking done (see task details)\n- Only pick up one task per heartbeat to avoid overloading\n- If a task is already `in_progress` and was started >2 hours ago with no progress update, reset it to backlog\n\n## Task Archive Maintenance\n- **Done tasks live in the Kanban Done column** — never remove them just because they're complete\n- Only archive done tasks older than 30 days to `data/tasks-archive.json`\n- When archiving: append to existing archive, remove from `tasks.json`, commit + push\n- The Done column should always show recent completions (last 30 days minimum)\n- Archive is for long-term storage only — the Kanban is the source of truth\n\n## Rule: Sub-agent Timeout\n- If a sub-agent runs for >5 minutes with no resolution, kill it and add the task to backlog\n- If the main agent spends >10 minutes debugging the same issue, stop and add to backlog\n- Always report what was tried and what the blocker is when adding to backlog\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1780298965759}}
{"type":"message","id":"9709b7d5","parentId":"0d7d291d","timestamp":"2026-06-01T07:29:45.915Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"5c5fdde0-ecde-495f-944f-2a929b28f8f7","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json') as f:\n  tasks = json.load(f)\nbacklog = [t for t in tasks if t['status'] == 'backlog']\nin_progress = [t for t in tasks if t['status'] == 'in_progress']\ndone = [t for t in tasks if t['status'] == 'done']\nprint(f'Total: {len(tasks)} | Backlog: {len(backlog)} | In Progress: {len(in_progress)} | Done: {len(done)}')\nif backlog:\n    t = backlog[0]\n    print(f'Next backlog task: [{t[\\\"priority\\\"]}] {t[\\\"title\\\"][:80]}')\nfor t in in_progress:\n    print(f'In progress: {t[\\\"title\\\"][:80]} (started: {t.get(\\\"startedAt\\\",\\\"?\\\")[:16]})')\n\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"python3 -c \\\"\\nimport json\\nwith open('/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json') as f:\\n  tasks = json.load(f)\\nbacklog = [t for t in tasks if t['status'] == 'backlog']\\nin_progress = [t for t in tasks if t['status'] == 'in_progress']\\ndone = [t for t in tasks if t['status'] == 'done']\\nprint(f'Total: {len(tasks)} | Backlog: {len(backlog)} | In Progress: {len(in_progress)} | Done: {len(done)}')\\nif backlog:\\n    t = backlog[0]\\n    print(f'Next backlog task: [{t[\\\\\\\"priority\\\\\\\"]}] {t[\\\\\\\"title\\\\\\\"][:80]}')\\nfor t in in_progress:\\n    print(f'In progress: {t[\\\\\\\"title\\\\\\\"][:80]} (started: {t.get(\\\\\\\"startedAt\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"?\\\\\\\")[:16]})')\\n\\\"\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":441,"output":214,"cacheRead":51200,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":51855,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780298965761,"responseId":"gen-1780298965-sO0Iie39NK