{"type":"message","id":"e7975a8b","parentId":"5962f35e","timestamp":"2026-06-01T07:31:19.225Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All three are stale tasks from mid-May with vague specs. The \"Error Feed\" and \"Task Completion\" ones need frontend work in the dashboard. \"Agent Office Overall\" is the biggest — it's the animation system.\n\nLet me pick up the \"Error Feed\" task since it's a concrete, bounded fix:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"c0df1f11-b66b-40b7-a60d-5bbf315f93fc","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\n\nwith open('/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json') as f:\n    tasks = json.load(f)\n\ntarget_id = None\nfor t in tasks:\n    if t['status'] == 'backlog' and t['assignee'] == 'lifesupport':\n        target_id = t['id']\n        break\n\nif target_id:\n    now = '2026-06-01T08:00:00.000Z'\n    for t in tasks:\n        if t['id'] == target_id:\n            t['status'] = 'in_progress'\n            t['startedAt'] = now\n            t['ts'] = 'just now'\n            t['lastUpdated'] = now\n            entry = {\n                'ts': now,\n                'action': 'started',\n                'actor': 'lifesupport',\n                'details': 'Status changed from backlog to in_progress'\n            }\n            t.setdefault('history', []).append(entry)\n            print(f'Started: {t[\\\"title\\\"]}')\n            break\n\n    with open('/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json', 'w') as f:\n        json.dump(tasks, f, indent=2)\n    print('tasks.json updated')\nelse:\n    print('Target not found')\n\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"python3 -c \\\"\\nimport json\\n\\nwith open('/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json') as f:\\n    tasks = json.load(f)\\n\\ntarget_id = None\\nfor t in tasks:\\n    if t['status'] == 'backlog' and t['assignee'] == 'lifesupport':\\n        target_id = t['id']\\n        break\\n\\nif target_id:\\n    now = '2026-06-01T08: