{"type":"message","id":"a4a7df36","parentId":"c6279085","timestamp":"2026-06-01T10:12:55.218Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"c24b99fb-56c9-4e77-a19c-89d57d09e7f5","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Current status: in_progress\nstartedAt: MISSING\nlast entries in history:\n  2026-06-01T08:00 reassigned by heartbeat: Reset from in_progress to backlog — stalled (started 2026-05-15T20:36 with no pr\n  2026-06-01T09:00 reassigned by heartbeat: Reset from in_progress to backlog — stale (started May 15, no progress)\n  2026-06-01T09:43 reassigned by heartbeat: Reset from in_progress to backlog — stalled (397h with no progress update)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":62,"aggregated":"Current status: in_progress\nstartedAt: MISSING\nlast entries in history:\n  2026-06-01T08:00 reassigned by heartbeat: Reset from in_progress to backlog — stalled (started 2026-05-15T20:36 with no pr\n  2026-06-01T09:00 reassigned by heartbeat: Reset from in_progress to backlog — stale (started May 15, no progress)\n  2026-06-01T09:43 reassigned by heartbeat: Reset from in_progress to backlog — stalled (397h with no progress update)","cwd":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780308775218}}
{"type":"message","id":"f0365e54","parentId":"a4a7df36","timestamp":"2026-06-01T10:13:08.158Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Wait — the history shows it was reset to backlog 3 times, but the current status is `in_progress` with no `startedAt`. Something is flipping it back. Let me check if a cron job or dispatcher is doing this:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"4b023847-a309-46fe-98f9-df646f8615b3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check if something else is writing to tasks.json\npython3 -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json') as f:\n    tasks = json.load(f)\nfor t in tasks:\n    if 'Error Feed' in t['title']:\n        print(json.dumps(t, indent=2))\n\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"# Check if something else is writing to tasks.json\\npython3 -c \\\"\\nimport json\\nwith open('/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json') as f:\\n    tasks = json.load(f)\\nfor t in tasks:\\n    if 'Error Feed' in t['title']:\\n        print(json.dumps(t, indent=2))\\n\\\"\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":435,"output":136,"cacheRead":54912,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":55483,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780308775220,"responseId":"gen-1780308775-C7Em4prd9bozRc4yso1Q"}}
{"type":"message","id":"13f1b6f8","parentId":"f0365e54","timestamp":"2026-06-01T10:13:08.237Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"4b023847-a309-46fe-98f9-df646f8615b3","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"id\": \"task-mp7cbyxz-0ztq\",\n  \"title\": \"Error Feed \\u2014 behaviour review and fix.\",\n  \"assignee\": \"lifesupport\",\n  \"status\": \"in_progress\",\n  \"priority\": \"P3\",\n  \"ts\": \"just now\",\n  \"note\": \"Error Feed \\u2014 behaviour review and fix.\\n\\nThe error feed currently has Investigate / Resolved / Skip buttons but \\nthe workflow is confusing. Here's how it should actually work:\\n\\n\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\nCORRECT ERROR FEED WORKFLOW\\n\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\n\\n1. A cron job fails \\u2192 error appears in the Error Feed tab with a \\n   \\\"NEW\\\" badge\\n\\n2. I click \\\"Investigate\\\" \\u2192 \\n   - The error status changes to \\\"IN PROGRESS\\\" \\n   - A corresponding task is automatically created in the Tasks \\n     section under \\\"In Progress\\\" so the crew knows to work on it\\n   - The error stays visible in the feed with an in-progress indicator\\n   - The button changes to show \\\"Resolved\\\" and \\\"Skip\\\"\\n\\n3. The crew fixes the underlying issue. The cron job runs successfully \\n   on its next scheduled run \\u2192\\n   - The error automatically clears from the Error Feed\\n   - The linked task in the Tasks section moves to \\\"Done\\\"\\n   - No manual \\\"Resolved\\\" click needed \\u2014 the system verified the fix\\n\\n4. If I click \\\"Resolved\\\" manually \\u2192\\n   - For when I've verified the fix myself\\n   - Error disappears from the feed\\n   - Linked task moves to Done\\n\\n5. If I click \\\"Skip\\\" \\u2192\\n   - For known non-critical issues I'm choosing to ignore\\n   - Error disappears from the feed\\n   - No task is created\\n\\n6. If the same job fails again later \\u2192\\n   - A NEW error appears (not the old one reopened)\\n   - Fresh timestamp, fresh status\\n   - Does NOT resurrect the old skipped/resolved error\\n\\n\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\nKEY RULES\\n\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\n\\n- Errors should NOT show \\\"Completed\\\" with an \\\"In Progress\\\" flag \\n  at the same time (current bug)\\n- When a cron job succeeds after being in error state, the error \\n  should auto-clear \\u2014 the system verified the fix\\n- The \\\"Investigate\\\" button creates a task in the Tasks board so \\n  work is tracked\\n- The error feed reflects REALITY: if the job is still failing, \\n  the error stays. If it succeeds, the error goes away.\\n- The cron job entry in the Scheduler list should show an error \\n  badge ONLY while there's an active unresolved error\\n\\n\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\nWHAT TO FIX NOW\\n\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\n\\n1. Fix the double-status bug (no more \\\"Completed\\\" + \\\"In Progress\\\" \\n   showing simultaneously)\\n2. Wire Investigate button to auto-create a task in the Tasks board\\n3. Wire cron job success to auto-clear the corresponding error\\n4. Wire cron job error badge to auto-clear when error is resolved\\n5. Confirm Skip behaviour works as described above\\n6. Test the full flow end-to-end\\n\\nReport what the current behaviour actually is, then fix it to \\nmatch this spec. [auto-dispatched 2026-06-01 08:53] [auto-dispatched 2026-06-01 09:53] [auto-dispatched 2026-06-01 10:23] [auto-dispatched 2026-06-01 10:53]\",\n  \"history\": [\n    {\n      \"ts\": \"2026-05-15T19:59:05.639Z\",\n      \"action\": \"created\",\n      \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n      \"details\": \"Task created\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"ts\": \"2026-05-15T19:59:07.177Z\",\n      \"action\": \"started\",\n      \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n      \"details\": \"Status changed from backlog to in_progress\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"ts\": \"2026-06-01T08:00:00.000Z\",\n      \"action\": \"reassigned\",\n      \"actor\": \"heartbeat\",\n      \"details\": \"Reset from in_progress to backlog \\u2014 stalled (started 2026-05-15T20:36 with no progress)\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"ts\": \"2026-06-01T09:00:00.000Z\",\n      \"action\": \"reassigned\",\n      \"actor\": \"heartbeat\",\n      \"details\": \"Reset from in_progress to backlog \\u2014 stale (started May 15, no progress)\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"ts\": \"2026-06-01T09:43:21.368763+00:00\",\n      \"action\": \"reassigned\",\n      \"actor\": \"heartbeat\",\n      \"details\": \"Reset from in_progress to backlog \\u2014 stalled (397h with no progress update)\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-06-01T09:43:21.368763+00:00\",\n  \"progress\": 40\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":54,"aggregated":"{\n  \"id\": \"task-mp7cbyxz-0ztq\",\n  \"title\": \"Error Feed \\u2014 behaviour review and fix.\",\n  \"assignee\": \"lifesupport\",\n  \"status\": \"in_progress\",\n  \"priority\": \"P3\",\n  \"ts\": \"just now\",\n  \"note\": \"Error Feed \\u2014 behaviour review and fix.\\n\\nThe error feed currently has Investigate / Resolved / Skip buttons but \\nthe workflow is confusing. Here's how it should actually work:\\n\\n\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\nCORRECT ERROR FEED WORKFLOW\\n\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\n\\n1. A cron job fails \\u2192 error appears in the Error Feed tab with a \\n   \\\"NEW\\\" badge\\n\\n2. I click \\\"Investigate\\\" \\u2192 \\n   - The error status changes to \\\"IN PROGRESS\\\" \\n   - A corresponding task is automatically created in the Tasks \\n     section under \\\"In Progress\\\" so the crew knows to work on it\\n   - The error stays visible in the feed with an in-progress indicator\\n   - The button changes to show \\\"Resolved\\\" and \\\"Skip\\\"\\n\\n3. The crew fixes the underlying issue. The cron job runs successfully \\n   on its next scheduled run \\u2192\\n   - The error automatically clears from the Error Feed\\n   - The linked task in the Tasks section moves to \\\"Done\\\"\\n   - No manual \\\"Resolved\\\" click needed \\u2014 the system verified the fix\\n\\n4. If I click \\\"Resolved\\\" manually \\u2192\\n   - For when I've verified the fix myself\\n   - Error disappears from the feed\\n   - Linked task moves to Done\\n\\n5. If I click \\\"Skip\\\" \\u2192\\n   - For known non-critical issues I'm choosing to ignore\\n   - Error disappears from the feed\\n   - No task is created\\n\\n6. If the same job fails again later \\u2192\\n   - A NEW error appears (not the old one reopened)\\n   - Fresh timestamp, fresh status\\n   - Does NOT resurrect the old skipped/resolved error\\n\\n\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\nKEY RULES\\n\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\n\\n- Errors should NOT show \\\"Completed\\\" with an \\\"In Progress\\\" flag \\n  at the same time (current bug)\\n- When a cron job succeeds after being in error state, the error \\n  should auto-clear \\u2014 the system verified the fix\\n- The \\\"Investigate\\\" button creates a task in the Tasks board so \\n  work is tracked\\n- The error feed reflects REALITY: if the job is still failing, \\n  the error stays. If it succeeds, the error goes away.\\n- The cron job entry in the Scheduler list should show an error \\n  badge ONLY while there's an active unresolved error\\n\\n\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\nWHAT TO FIX NOW\\n\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\n\\n1. Fix the double-status bug (no more \\\"Completed\\\" + \\\"In Progress\\\" \\n   showing simultaneously)\\n2. Wire Investigate button to auto-create a task in the Tasks board\\n3. Wire cron job success to auto-clear the corresponding error\\n4. Wire cron job error badge to auto-clear when error is resolved\\n5. Confirm Skip behaviour works as described above\\n6. Test the full flow end-to-end\\n\\nReport what the current 