{"type":"message","id":"c204ff40","parentId":"4c181331","timestamp":"2026-06-01T10:13:59.083Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Only 3 cron jobs, none related to task dispatching. The `[auto-dispatched]` tags in the note must be from the Kanban's own dispatch mechanism — when a task is moved to In Progress, the frontend calls `/api/dispatch` which writes to `queue.json`. But that shouldn't change the task status back to `in_progress`.\n\nLet me check if the queue has entries for this task:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"0f6f329a-8ff5-415f-a94c-3b3d64cea203","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/workspace/data/queue.json | python3 -c \"\nimport json, sys\ndata = json.load(sys.stdin)\nfor item in data:\n    if 'Error' in item.get('title','') or 'lifesupport' in item.get('assignee',''):\n        print(json.dumps(item, indent=2))\n\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cat ~/.openclaw/workspace/data/queue.json | python3 -c \\\"\\nimport json, sys\\ndata = json.load(sys.stdin)\\nfor item in data:\\n    if 'Error' in item.get('title','') or 'lifesupport' in item.get('assignee',''):\\n        print(json.dumps(item, indent=2))\\n\\\"\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":319,"output":170,"cacheRead":57856,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":58345,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780308824572,"responseId":"gen-1780308824-QJltXoPizXyd4JF8VzGA"}}
