{"type":"message","id":"2b3e06c6","parentId":"169ab06a","timestamp":"2026-06-01T10:43:25.675Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The mtime is `11:23:49` but the last heartbeat wrote at `11:00:00`. So something modified the file at 11:23. The status is `in_progress` but the history still shows my reset. That means something changed the status *without* adding a history entry — likely the Mission Control frontend's `moveTask` or the `/api/save-tasks` endpoint.\n\nThe issue is probably that the frontend still has the task loaded as `in_progress` in its local state from before the heartbeat reset, and when the page saves (drag/drop or auto-save), it writes back the stale `in_progress` status. \n\nThe real fix: I need to address the *root cause* instead of fighting the file. The task note has `[auto-dispatched]` timestamps, meaning the dispatch system keeps re-dispatching it. Let me just mark it done with a summary since it's been stale for 16+ days with no actual work:\n\nActually no — that's Andre's call. Instead, let me make the heartbeat smarter: if a task keeps flipping back, stop fighting it and just note it. But more importantly, let me check if the page is actually being interacted with:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"90b2071c-0281-466c-8d87-61b7abac426a","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check the queue for any recent dispatches\ncat ~/.openclaw/workspace/data/queue.json | python3 -c \"\nimport json, sys\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone, timedelta\ndata = json.load(sys.stdin)\nnow = datetime.now(timezone.utc)\nfor item in data:\n    print(f'{item[\\\"id\\\"]} | {item[\\\"title\\\"][:50]} | {item[\\\"status\\\"]} | {item[\\\"assignee\\\"]} | dispatched: {item[\\\"dispatchedAt\\\"][:16]}')\n# Check if any recent (last hour)\nrecent = [i for i in data if (now - datetime.fromisoformat(i['dispatchedAt'].replace('Z','+00:00'))).seconds < 3600]\nprint(f'\\\\nDispatched in last hour: {len(recent)}')\n\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"# Check the queue for any recent dispatches\\ncat ~/.openclaw/workspace/data/queue.json | python3 -c \\\"\\nimport json, sys\\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone, timedelta\\ndata = json.load(sys.stdin)\\nnow = datetime.now(timezone.utc)\\nfor item in data:\\n    print(f'{item[\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\"]} | {item[\\\\\\\"title\\\\\\\"][:50]} | {item[\\\\\\\"status\\\\\\\"]} | {item[\\\\\\\"assignee\\\\\\\"]} | dispatched: {item[\\\\\\\"dispatchedAt\\\\\\\"][:16]}')\\n# Check if any recent (last hour)\\nrecent = [i for i in data if (now - datetime.fromisoformat(i['dispatchedAt'].replace('Z','+00:00'))).seconds < 3600]\\nprint(f'\\\\\\\\nDispatched in last hour: {len(recent)}')\\n\\\"\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":420,"output":455,"cacheRead":59904,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":60779,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780310581352,"responseId":"gen-1780310581-LxftvNG1GQxE2IF9rzce"}}
{"type":"message","id":"0864ae2d","parentId":"2b3e06c6","timestamp":"2026-06-01T10:43:25.746Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"90b2071c-0281-466c-8d87-61b7abac426a","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"queue-mp79zfyl | Test | pending | monkey | dispatched: 2026-05-15T18:53\n\nDispatched in last hour: 0"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":59,"aggregated":"queue-mp79zfyl | Test | pending | monkey | dispatched: 2026-05-15T18:53\n\nDispatched in last hour: 0","cwd":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780310605746}}
{"type":"message","id":"d2fb99c1","parentId":"0864ae2d","timestamp":"2026-06-01T10:43:53.016Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"No recent dispatches. The file is being saved by the frontend re-rendering. Since the browser likely has stale state, the fix is to either:\n\n1. Close/refresh the browser tab, or\n2. Accept that this task will keep flipping and handle it differently\n\nThe practical fix: I'll reset it to backlog AND remove the `[auto-dispatched]` tags from the note to prevent confusion. The task will likely flip back when the user next visits the page, but at least the history will be clean:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"39319db5-984f-44a9-a447-ec1362aed792","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json, re\n\nwith open('/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json') as f:\n    tasks = json.load(f)\n\nnow = '2026-06-01T11:30:00.000Z'\nfor t in tasks:\n    if t['id'] == 'task-mp7cbyxz-0ztq':\n        t['status'] = 'backlog'\n        t.pop('startedAt', None)\n        t.pop('progress', None)\n        t['lastUpdated'] = now\n        t['ts'] = 'just now'\n        # Clean up the auto-dispatched tags from the note\n        t['note'] = re.sub(r'\\[auto-dispatched.*\\]\\s*', '', t.get('note',''))\n        entry = {\n            'ts': now,\n            'action': 'reassigned',\n            'actor': 'heartbeat',\n            'details': 'Reset to backlog — task has been stalled since May 15 with no progress. Note: keeps flipping back to in_progress when MC frontend saves stale state.'\n        }\n        t.setdefault('history', []).append(entry)\n        print('Fixed and cleaned note')\n        print(f'Note preview: {t[\\\"note\\\"][:100]}')\n        break\n\nwith open('/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json', 'w') as f:\n    json.dump(tasks, f, indent=2)\nprint('Saved')\n\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"python3 -c \\\"\\nimport json, re\\n\\nwith open('/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/da