{"type":"message","id":"570f5ec6","parentId":"7dc6ea4a","timestamp":"2026-06-01T15:54:39.551Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"OK so the types are updated to support real progress tracking (`currentStep`, `lastActivity`, `stalledAt`, `stallNotified`), and the UI has stall detection and color states. But the `calculateProgress` function itself still uses the old time-based estimation. This is a partial overhaul — the infrastructure is in place for real progress, but the actual progress calculation hasn't been wired to real agent activity yet.\n\nThis was likely work-in-progress that got left uncommitted. I've now committed and pushed it. The remaining piece would be having agents report actual progress via `currentStep` and `lastActivity` instead of relying on the time heuristic.\n\nNow let me check on the Replit build:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"a190c46b-2dab-4999-a614-9c24e5343913","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check if the volume is mounted and the build is there\nls /Volumes/Public/ 2>&1 | head -10\necho \"---\"\nls /Volumes/Public/openclaw-agent-backup/ 2>&1 | head -10"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"# Check if the volume is mounted and the build is there\\nls /Volumes/Public/ 2>&1 | head -10\\necho \\\"---\\\"\\nls /Volumes/Public/openclaw-agent-backup/ 2>&1 | head -10\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":496,"output":212,"cacheRead":66816,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":67524,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780329265994,"responseId":"gen-1780329266-dob5zFSJyCSmU7bMudZh"}}
