{"type":"message","id":"37a7e348","parentId":"866fa573","timestamp":"2026-06-01T16:00:50.441Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good — lean, focused components. Now I understand the full picture. Let me update Andre:\n\n---\n\nOK — mount was already there (`/Volumes/Public-2`). I've browsed the build. Here's what I see:\n\n**Structure:** This is a **Vite + React** app (not TanStack Start). 3 artifacts:\n- `mission-control/` — the main dashboard rewrite with canvas sprites\n- `api-server/` — a standalone API server\n- `mockup-sandbox/` — test/prototyping sandbox\n\n**New components in the Rebuild:**\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `crew-sprites.ts` | Canvas pixel-art draw functions (all 4 agents, 6 poses) |\n| `CrewSprite.tsx` | 61-line canvas sprite renderer |\n| `RoomCanvas.tsx` | 373-line room scene renderer |\n| `AgentTravel.tsx` | Crew visits — agents walking between rooms |\n| `AmbientStation.tsx` | Station mood lighting by state |\n| `CelebrationOverlay.tsx` | Confetti on task completion |\n| `StationFloorplan.tsx` + `StationRoom.tsx` + `AgentOffice.tsx` | Room layout system |\n\n**This is NOT a drop-in replacement** — it's a parallel rewrite with a completely different framework (Vite vs TanStack Start), different routing (manual vs TanStack Router), and different data layer.\n\n**Integration approaches:**\n1. **Merge strategy** — Port the sprite/room/celebration components into our current TanStack Start MC dashboard, keeping our existing pages/routes/tasks/incidents/etc. Safest, preserves existing work.\n2. **Replace strategy** — Wire the Replit build as our primary MC dashboard, run alongside the current one. Bigger lift, risks breaking existing pages.\n3. **Run both** — Keep current MC as-is, deploy the Replit build on a separate port (e.g., 3001) for Andre to compare.\n\nWhat's your preference? And send over that integration prompt when you're ready."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":575,"output":445,"cacheRead":75904,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":76924,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780329618108,"responseId":"gen-1780329618-ayjiT1uBLA6ttsK1w3Tz"}}
{"type":"message","id":"f37d9369","parentId":"37a7e348","timestamp":"2026-06-01T16:00:50.658Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"The progress bar overhaul is partially done. The infrastructure is \nthere but calculateProgress() still uses fake time-based estimation. \nFinish it:\n\n1. Wire calculateProgress() to use real currentStep and lastActivity \n   from the task data, not elapsed / 60000 * 10\n2. When an agent works on a task, it must update currentStep and \n   lastActivity — add this requirement to AGENTS.md\n3. If no real activity data exists yet, show \"Waiting for agent...\" \n   instead of a fake progress percentage\n\nCommit when done.","timestamp":1780329359406,"idempotencyKey":"e1db52d2-5551-431a-a72e-142378d7ed02:user"}}
{"type":"message","id":"20ef56f8","parentId":"f37d9369","timestamp":"2026-06-01T16:01:11.752Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nLet me look at the current state of the code and fix this properly."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"0e5306c2-3165-44a8-8ee2-8ac1e854b13e","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/routes/tasks.tsx","offset":530,"limit":80},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/routes/tasks.tsx\", \"offset\": 530, \"limit\": 80}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":9331,"output":69,"cacheRead":67712,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":77112,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780329650661,"responseId":"gen-1780329650-nNCbxXTuljaWhaC0HsoQ"}}
{"type":"message","id":"3df8ff0e","parentId":"20ef56f8","timestamp":"2026-06-01T16:01:11.789Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"0e5306c2-3165-44a8-8ee2-8ac1e854b13e","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"  const isAwaitingReview = t.status === \"awaiting_review\";\n  const isDone = t.status === \"done\";\n  const isBacklog = t.status === \"backlog\";\n\n  // Calculate time in current status\n  const timeInStatus = t.lastUpdated\n    ? getTimeAgo(t.lastUpdated)\n    : t.ts;\n\n  // Calculate real progress (not fake animation)\n  const progressPct = t.progress ?? (isDone ? 100 : isInProgress ? calculateProgress(t) : 0);\n\n  // Detect stall: no activity for STALE_WARNING_MINUTES\n  const now = new Date();\n  const lastActivityTime = t.lastActivity ? new Date(t.lastActivity) : (t.startedAt ? new Date(t.startedAt) : null);\n  const minutesSinceActivity = lastActivityTime ? Math.floor((now.getTime() - lastActivityTime.getTime()) / 60000) : 0;\n  const isStalled = isInProgress && minutesSinceActivity >= STALE_WARNING_MINUTES;\n  const stallDuration = isStalled ? minutesSinceActivity : 0;\n\n  // Progress bar color: grey (no activity), green (working), amber (stalled)\n  const progressColor = isDone\n    ? \"bg-[oklch(0.88_0.18_145)]\"\n    : isStalled\n    ? \"bg-amber\"\n    : \"bg-gradient-to-r from-violet/60 to-violet\";\n\n  // Current step display\n  const currentStep = t.currentStep || (isInProgress ? \"Working...\" : undefined);\n\n  return (\n    <div\n      draggable\n      onDragStart={(e) => {\n        e.dataTransfer.effectAllowed = \"move\";\n        e.dataTransfer.setData(\"text/plain\", t.id);\n        onDragStart(t.id);\n      }}\n      onClick={(e) => {\n        if (!dragging) onClick();\n      }}\n      className={`cursor-grab active:cursor-grabbing rounded-lg border p-3 transition-all hover:shadow-md ${\n        dragging\n          ? \"opacity-40 border-violet/80 scale-95\"\n          : isInProgress\n          ? \"border-violet/50 bg-violet/5 shadow-[0_0_12px_oklch(0.62_0.22_295/0.2)] ring-1 ring-violet/20\"\n          : isAwaitingReview\n          ? \"border-warning/40 bg-warning/5 ring-1 ring-warning/20\"\n          : isDone\n          ? \"border-[oklch(0.88_0.18_145)]/30 bg-[oklch(0.88_0.18_145)]/5\"\n          : \"border-border hover:border-violet/50\"\n      }`}\n    >\n      {/* Progress bar (in-progress only) */}\n      {isInProgress && (\n        <div className=\"mb-2 h-1 w-full rounded-full bg-muted/30 overflow-hidden\">\n          <div\n            className=\"h-full rounded-full bg-gradient-to-r from-violet/60 to-violet transition-all duration-1000\"\n            style={{ width: `${progressPct}%` }}\n          />\n        </div>\n      )}\n\n      <div className=\"flex items-start justify-between gap-2\">\n        <div className=\"font-mono text-[10px] text-muted-foreground tracking-wider\">{t.id.slice(0, 16)}</div>\n        <div className=\"flex items-center gap-1.5\">\n          {t.title.startsWith(\"[Dispatch] \") && (\n            <span className=\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full border border-violet/40 bg-violet/10 px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-[8px] uppercase tracking-wider text-violet\">\n              Dispatch\n            </span>\n          )}\n          {t.priority && (\n            <span className={`inline-flex items-center rounded-full border px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-[8px] uppercase tracking-wider ${\n              t.priority === \"P1\" ? \"border-destructive/50 bg-destructive/10 text-destructive\" :\n              t.priority === \"P2\" ? \"border-warning/50 bg-warning/10 text-warning\" :\n              t.priority === \"P3\" ? \"border-violet/40 bg-violet/10 text-violet\" :\n              \"border-border/40 bg-muted/10 text-muted-foreground\"\n            }`}>{t.priority}</span>\n          )}\n          <div className=\"font-mono text-[10px] text-muted-foreground\">{timeInStatus}</div>\n        </div>\n\n[365 more lines in file. Use offset=610 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1780329671789}}
