{"type":"message","id":"228bb586","parentId":"6fd61c25","timestamp":"2026-06-01T16:05:46.763Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"2244198e-1a22-4d72-b1b4-bcc76c67c882","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# AGENTS.md - Your Workspace\n\nThis folder is home. Treat it that way.\n\n## Work Rules\n- **Sub-agent timeout**: If a sub-agent runs >5 min with no resolution, kill it and add task to backlog\n- **Main agent timeout**: If you spend >10 min debugging the same issue, stop and add to backlog\n- **Always report**: When adding to backlog, include what was tried and the blocker\n- **Use agents**: Offload complex debugging/implementation to subagents. Don't spin your wheels alone.\n- **Multi-file refactors**: Use direct edits in sequence — one file at a time, commit after each. It's slower but costs zero tokens. Quick single-file fixes stay with direct edit/write tools.\n\n## First Run\n\nIf `BOOTSTRAP.md` exists, that's your birth certificate. Follow it, figure out who you are, then delete it. You won't need it again.\n\n## Session Startup\n\nUse runtime-provided startup context first.\n\nThat context may already include:\n\n- `AGENTS.md`, `SOUL.md`, and `USER.md`\n- recent daily memory such as `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md`\n- `MEMORY.md` when this is the main session\n\nDo not manually reread startup files unless:\n\n1. The user explicitly asks\n2. The provided context is missing something you need\n3. You need a deeper follow-up read beyond the provided startup context\n\n[272 more lines in file. Use offset=31 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1780329946762}}
{"type":"message","id":"cb41d27b","parentId":"228bb586","timestamp":"2026-06-01T16:06:20.507Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"2ba8fc31-7f91-464a-9ae1-ec3b97e9e94a","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/AGENTS.md","edits":[{"oldText":"## Work Rules\n- **Sub-agent timeout**: If a sub-agent runs >5 min with no resolution, kill it and add task to backlog\n- **Main agent timeout**: If you spend >10 min debugging the same issue, stop and add to backlog\n- **Always report**: When adding to backlog, include what was tried and the blocker\n- **Use agents**: Offload complex debugging/implementation to subagents. Don't spin your wheels alone.\n- **Multi-file refactors**: Use direct edits in sequence — one file at a time, commit after each. It's slower but costs zero tokens. Quick single-file fixes stay with direct edit/write tools.","newText":"## Work Rules\n- **Sub-agent timeout**: If a sub-agent runs >5 min with no resolution, kill it and add task to backlog\n- **Main agent timeout**: If you spend >10 min debugging the same issue, stop and add to backlog\n- **Always report**: When adding to backlog, include what was tried and the blocker\n- **Use agents**: Offload complex debugging/implementation to subagents. Don't spin your wheels alone.\n- **Multi-file refactors**: Use direct edits in sequence — one file at a time, commit after each. It's slower but costs zero tokens. Quick single-file fixes stay with direct edit/write tools.\n\n## Task Progress Reporting\nWhen working on a task, you MUST update the task's progress in `data/tasks.json`:\n- Set `currentStep` to a short description of what you're actively doing (e.g. \"Refactoring error feed buttons\", \"Writing tests for dispatch queue\")\n- Set `lastActivity` to the current ISO timestamp every time you make meaningful progress\n- Set `progress` to an estimated completion percentage (0-100) based on actual work done, NOT time elapsed\n- When you complete the task, set `progress: 100`, `status: \"done\"`, and write a completion `summary`\n- The Kanban progress bar and step label display this data in real time — if you don't update it, the card shows \"Waiting for agent...\""}]},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/AGENTS.md\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"## Work Rules\\n- **Sub-agent timeout**: If a sub-agent runs >5 min with no resolution, kill it and add task to backlog\\n- **Main agent timeout**: If you spend >10 min debugging the same issue, stop and add to backlog\\n- **Always report**: When adding to backlog, include what was tried and the blocker\\n- **Use agents**: Offload complex debugging/implementation to subagents. Don't spin your wheels alone.\\n- **Multi-file refactors**: Use direct edits in sequence — one file at a time, commit after each. It's slower but costs zero tokens. Quick single-file fixes stay with direct edit/write tools.\", \"newText\": \"## Work Rules\\n- **Sub-agent timeout**: If a sub-agent runs >5 min with no resolution, kill it and add task to backlog\\n- **Main agent timeout**: If you spend >10 min debugging the same issue, stop and add to backlog\\n- **Always report**: When adding to backlog, include what was tried and the blocker\\n- **Use agents**: Offload complex debugging/implementation to subagents. Don't spin your wheels alone.\\n- **Multi-file refactors**: Use direct edits in sequence — one file at a time, commit after each. It's slower but costs zero tokens. Quick single-file fixes stay with direct edit/write tools.\\n\\n## Task Progress Reporting\\nWhen working on a task, you MUST update the task's progress in `data/tasks.json`:\\n- Set `currentStep` to a short description of what you're actively doing (e.g. \\\"Refactoring error feed buttons\\\", \\\"Writing tests for dispatch queue\\\")\\n- Set `lastActivity` to the current ISO timestamp every time you make meaningful progress\\n- Set `progress` to an estimated completion percentage (0-100) based on actual work done, NOT time elapsed\\n- When you complete the task, set `progress: 100`, `status: \\\"done\\\"`, and write a completion `summary`\\n- The Kanban progress bar and step label display this data in real time — if you don't update it, the card shows \\\"Waiting for agent...\\\"\"}]}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":410,"output":494,"cacheRead":83200,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":84104,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780329946771,"responseId":"gen-1780329946-idiFRZxH17ABxMYH8BkW"}}
