{"type":"message","id":"ea702e70","parentId":"77f08ede","timestamp":"2026-06-01T16:09:09.182Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Here's what changed:\n\n**`calculateProgress()` — no more fake time estimation:**\n- If `t.progress` is explicitly set by an agent → use it (clamped 0-100)\n- If `currentStep` + `lastActivity` exist → derive from recency (75% active now, 60% recent, 50% stale)\n- Otherwise → return 0, which triggers \"Waiting for agent...\" in the UI\n\n**Progress bar UI:**\n- **No real data:** tiny pulsing grey dot + \"Waiting for agent...\" label\n- **Active agent:** green bar at real % + step label in violet\n- **Stalled (30+ min no activity):** amber bar\n- **Badge:** \"WORKING\" (violet) when real data exists, \"WAITING\" (grey) when not\n\n**`moveTask` now seeds initial data** when moving to In Progress — sets `lastActivity` to now and `currentStep` to \"Agent starting…\" so the card doesn't flash \"Waiting\" on the first render.\n\n**AGENTS.md updated** with the progress reporting requirement: agents must set `currentStep`, `lastActivity`, and `progress` when working on tasks.\n\nBoth repos committed. MC dashboard pushed to GitHub. ✅"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":156,"output":280,"cacheRead":85760,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":86196,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780330120040,"responseId":"gen-1780330120-Wz3vHL3gykBDLk5IOa6T"}}
