{"type":"message","id":"3b91d0cf","parentId":"3ddbf333","timestamp":"2026-06-01T20:43:20.703Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Ah, you're trying to automate the **Ollie food delivery app** on iPhone! That's a mobile app, so the approach is different from Mac browser automation.\n\nHere's the reality:\n\n**What I can't do right now:**\n- Control a native iOS app on a physical iPhone — no tool currently supports that\n- Screen-record and \"tap\" on your Mac's display of the iPhone screen (it's just mirroring, not interactive)\n\n**What you could do:**\n\n**Option 1: iPhone Shortcuts + my automation**\nIf Ollie has any web-based component or API, I could help build an automation that triggers from your Mac (which then sends notifications to your phone via the Gateway).\n\n**Option 2: Mac Virtual Display + browser automation**\nIf Ollie has a web app (not just iOS), I could automate the entire flow in a browser window on your Mac — select food, set time, post, wait, repeat.\n\n**Option 3: Accessibility + UI scripting (hacky but possible for Mac)**\nIf you run Ollie through a **simulator or Catalyst app** on Mac, I could theoretically use AppleScript or `cliclick` (a Mac command-line tool for mouse/keyboard simulation) to automate taps and inputs. But this is fragile and breaks easily.\n\n**The real question:** Is Ollie just an iOS app, or does it have a web/app on other platforms? If it's iOS-only, the most reliable path would be something like **TrollStore + AutoTouch** on a jailbroken iPhone, or a dedicated automation device — but that's outside my wheelhouse.\n\nWhat's the goal — are you trying to batch-order food, or is this a grinder/strategy thing? Knowing the objective might reveal a simpler path."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":640,"output":369,"cacheRead":86784,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":87793,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780346581005,"responseId":"gen-1780346581-9FiaCHOsl2sOsKTXpCx1"}}
{"type":"message","id":"c5e7d24f","parentId":"3b91d0cf","timestamp":"2026-06-01T21:01:17.126Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"leave this for now, how did the below go?\n\nThe progress bar overhaul is partially done. The infrastructure is \nthere but calculateProgress() still uses fake time-based estimation. \nFinish it:\n\n1. Wire calculateProgress() to use real currentStep and lastActivity \n   from the task data, not elapsed / 60000 * 10\n2. When an agent works on a task, it must update currentStep and \n   lastActivity — add this requirement to AGENTS.md\n3. If no real activity data exists yet, show \"Waiting for agent...\" \n   instead of a fake progress percentage\n\nCommit when done.","timestamp":1780347676968,"idempotencyKey":"74cb1418-7157-4991-a698-661dffae5410:user"}}
{"type":"message","id":"91818015","parentId":"c5e7d24f","timestamp":"2026-06-01T21:01:50.702Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"That's done and pushed! ✅\n\nHere's what landed:\n\n**`calculateProgress()` — fully rewired:**\n- Uses explicit `progress` value if set by agent (0-100 clamped)\n- Derives from `currentStep` + `lastActivity` recency if available (75% / 60% / 50%)\n- Returns 0 when no real data → triggers \"Waiting for agent...\" in the UI\n\n**Progress bar UI changes:**\n- Pulsing grey dot + \"Waiting for agent...\" label when no activity\n- Green bar with step label when agent is actively reporting\n- Amber bar for stalled tasks (30+ min no update)\n- Badge switches between \"WORKING\" and \"WAITING\" accordingly\n\n**`moveTask` seeds initial state** — when moving to In Progress, sets `currentStep: \"Agent starting…\"` and `lastActivity: now` so the card doesn't flash empty.\n\n**AGENTS.md updated** with the progress reporting requirement.\n\nTwo commits pushed:\n- `1415e56` — progress bar wiring + UI (MC dashboard, on GitHub)\n- `40a8bef` — AGENTS.md update (workspace repo)\n\nReady for the Replit Crew-New build integration whenever you are."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":86899,"output":274,"cacheRead":1024,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":88197,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780347677131,"responseId":"gen-1780347677-AMM86p4L5OFtpHgrgTfv"}}
