{"type":"message","id":"c6218625","parentId":"5db6a048","timestamp":"2026-06-01T21:19:42.980Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"Option A — port the sprite system into our live build. Do NOT replace \nthe entire app. Extract only these specific files from the Replit build:\n\nCORE — must port:\n1. crew-sprites.ts — canvas sprite draw functions (all 4 agents, 6 poses)\n2. CrewSprite.tsx — canvas sprite component with requestAnimationFrame\n3. RoomCanvas.tsx — canvas room scenes with animated overlays\n4. StationFloorplan.tsx — crew visits with walking animations\n5. AgentOffice.tsx — the main office view with all wiring\n6. AmbientStation.tsx — mood lighting (calm/busy/alert/critical)\n7. RoomAmbient.tsx — per-room ambient effects\n8. CelebrationOverlay.tsx — confetti on task completion\n9. delights.ts — station chatter rotation (if new)\n\nDO NOT PORT:\n- Wouter router — we use TanStack Router\n- server-data.ts — Replit version has hardcoded mock data\n- Any \"coming soon\" placeholder pages\n- package.json or build config\n- The Vite SPA structure — we're TanStack Start SSR\n\nIntegration:\n1. Copy the files into our live build at \n   ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/\n2. Resolve any import conflicts (Wouter → TanStack Router)\n3. Replace the current PNG sprite system with CrewSprite\n4. Wire RoomCanvas into StationRoom\n5. Keep ALL existing pages intact — Tasks, Scheduler, Incidents, \n   Settings, Teams\n6. Keep ALL real data connections — no mock data\n\nVerify:\n- All routes return 200\n- Sprites render on Dashboard and /visual\n- Crew visits work without duplicate sprites\n- Mood lighting responds to station state\n- No TypeScript errors\n\nCommit after each file integrated successfully.","timestamp":1780348782848,"idempotencyKey":"38c81117-3668-45f4-9bd6-0efc9a2da458:user"}}
