{"type":"message","id":"6097fc6d","parentId":"db2d2718","timestamp":"2026-06-01T21:34:55.819Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"06f12f16-b9dd-4688-ac89-4bb314d84dfa","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The plugin \"vite-tsconfig-paths\" is detected. Vite now supports tsconfig paths resolution natively via the resolve.tsconfigPaths option. You can remove the plugin and set resolve.tsconfigPaths: true in your Vite config instead.\nWarning: Route file \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/routes/api/cron-errors.ts\" does not export a Route. This file will not be included in the route tree.\n\nIf this file is not intended to be a route, you can exclude it using one of these options:\n  1. Rename the file to \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/routes/api/-cron-errors.ts\" (prefix with \"-\")\n  2. Use 'routeFileIgnorePattern' in your config to match this file\n\nCurrent configuration:\n  routeFileIgnorePrefix: \"-\"\n  routeFileIgnorePattern: undefined\nWarning: Route file \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/routes/api/cron-toggle.ts\" does not export a Route. This file will not be included in the route tree.\n\nIf this file is not intended to be a route, you can exclude it using one of these options:\n  1. Rename the file to \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/routes/api/-cron-toggle.ts\" (prefix with \"-\")\n  2. Use 'routeFileIgnorePattern' in your config to match this file\n\nCurrent configuration:\n  routeFileIgnorePrefix: \"-\"\n  routeFileIgnorePattern: undefined\nWarning: Route file \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/routes/api/crons.ts\" does not export a Route. This file will not be included in the route tree.\n\nIf this file is not intended to be a route, you can exclude it using one of these options:\n  1. Rename the file to \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/routes/api/-crons.ts\" (prefix with \"-\")\n  2. Use 'routeFileIgnorePattern' in your config to match this file\n\nCurrent configuration:\n  routeFileIgnorePrefix: \"-\"\n  routeFileIgnorePattern: undefined\nWarning: Route file \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/routes/api/incidents-update.ts\" does not export a Route. This file will not be included in the route tree.\n\nIf this file is not intended to be a route, you can exclude it using one of these options:\n  1. Rename the file to \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/routes/api/-incidents-update.ts\" (prefix with \"-\")\n  2. Use 'routeFileIgnorePattern' in your config to match this file\n\nCurrent configuration:\n  routeFileIgnorePrefix: \"-\"\n  routeFileIgnorePattern: undefined\nWarning: Route file \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/routes/api/incidents-create.ts\" does not export a Route. This file will not be included in the route tree.\n\nIf this file is not intended to be a route, you can exclude it using one of these options:\n  1. Rename the file to \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/routes/api/-incidents-create.ts\" (prefix with \"-\")\n  2. Use 'routeFileIgnorePattern' in your config to match this file\n\nCurrent configuration:\n  routeFileIgnorePrefix: \"-\"\n  routeFileIgnorePattern: undefined\nWarning: Route file \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/routes/api/dispatch.ts\" does not export a Route. This file will not be included in the route tree.\n\nIf this file is not intended to be a route, you can exclude it using one of these options:\n  1. Rename the file to \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/routes/api/-dispatch.ts\" (prefix with \"-\")\n  2. Use 'routeFileIgnorePattern' in your config to match this file\n\nCurrent configuration:\n  routeFileIgnorePrefix: \"-\"\n  routeFileIgnorePattern: undefined\nWarning: Route file \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/routes/api/tasks-add.ts\" does not export a Route. This file will not be included in the route tree.\n\nIf this file is not intended to be a route, you can exclude it using one of these options:\n  1. Rename the file to \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/routes/api/-tasks-add.ts\" (prefix with \"-\")\n  2. Use 'routeFileIgnorePattern' in your config to match this file\n\nCurrent configuration:\n  routeFileIgnorePrefix: \"-\"\n  routeFileIgnorePattern: undefined\nWarning: Route file \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/routes/api/save-tasks.ts\" does not export a Route. This file will not be included in the route tree.\n\nIf this file is not intended to be a route, you can exclude it using one of these options:\n  1. Rename the file to \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/routes/api/-save-tasks.ts\" (prefix with \"-\")\n  2. Use 'routeFileIgnorePattern' in your config to match this file\n\nCurrent configuration:\n  routeFileIgnorePrefix: \"-\"\n  routeFileIgnorePattern: undefined\nPort 3000 is in use, trying another one...\nPort 3001 is in use, trying another one...\nPort 3002 is in use, trying another one...\n\n  VITE v8.0.13  ready in 673 ms\n\n  ➜  Local:   http://localhost:3003/\n  ➜  Network: http://192.168.68.64:3003/\nReferenceError: AnimatePresence is not defined at StationChatter in Dashboard.tsx. The awaitingReviewCount variable was defined inside QuickActionsPanel but referenced in the parent Dashboard component — a scoping bug causing SSR crash on the /visual page.\",tags:$R[193]=[\"ssr\",\"animation\",\"build\",\"dashboard\",\"backfill-2026-05-16\"],timeline:$R[194]=[$R[195]={ts:\"2026-05-16T14:36:26.000Z\",message:\"Backfilled from logs by backfill-2026-05-16\",actor:\"system\"}],actions:$R[196]=[]},$R[197]={id:\"INC-006\",title:\"Port conflict — Mission Control dev server jumping between 3000 and 3001\",severity:\"P3\",status:\"TRIAGE\",owner:\"engineer\",acknowledged:!1,escalated:!1,opened:\"2026-05-16T14:36:26.000Z\",lastActivity:\"2026-05-16T14:36:26.000Z\",summary:\"When the LaunchAgent restarts the dev server, it sometimes finds port 3000 still occupied by the previous process and falls back to 3001. This causes confusion about which port is serving the live app and can result in stale builds being served.\",tags:$R[198]=[\"dev-server\",\"launchagent\",\"conflict\",\"port\",\"backfill-2026-05-16\"],timeline:$R[199]=[$R[200]={ts:\"2026-05-16T14:36:26.000Z\",message:\"Backfilled from logs by backfill-2026-05-16\",actor:\"system\"}],actions:$R[201]=[]},$R[202]={id:\"INC-005\",title:\"Disk space warning — Data volume at 85% (175 Gi / 228 Gi)\",severity:\"P3\",status:\"TRIAGE\",owner:\"lifesupport\",acknowledged:!1,escalated:!1,opened:\"2026-05-16T14:36:26.000Z\",lastActivity:\"2026-05-16T14:36:26.000Z\",summary:\"Health log from 2026-05-15 12:03 shows /System/Volumes/Data at 85% usage (175 Gi / 228 Gi). Swap/compressor usage notable at ~21.9 GB. Approaching threshold where system performance may degrade.\",tags:$R[203]=[\"swap\",\"disk\",\"warning\",\"storage\",\"backfill-2026-05-16\"],timeline:$R[204]=[$R[205]={ts:\"2026-05-16T14:36:26.000Z\",message:\"Backfilled from logs by backfill-2026-05-16\",actor:\"system\"}],actions:$R[206]=[]},$R[207]={id:\"INC-004\",title:\"Memory index corruption after session restart\",severity:\"P1\",status:\"MITIGATING\",owner:\"archivist\",opened:\"2026-05-12 09:14\",summary:\"After an unplanned session restart, the SQLite memory index became partially corrupted. Daily log entries from 2026-05-11 onwards were not searchable. The raw .md files are intact — only the index needs rebuilding.\",tags:$R[208]=[\"memory\",\"corruption\",\"indexing\",\"urgent\"],timeline:$R[209]=[$R[210]={ts:\"09:14\",message:\"Incident auto-detected: memory search returning stale results\",actor:\"lifesupport\"},$R[211]={ts:\"09:22\",message:\"Confirmed SQLite index mismatch — 14 entries missing from index\",actor:\"archivist\"},$R[212]={ts:\"09:31\",message:\"Status escalated to MITIGATING, assigned to Archivist\",actor:\"monkey\"},$R[213]={ts:\"09:45\",message:\"Raw .md files verified intact, index rebuild initiated\",actor:\"archivist\"},$R[214]={ts:\"10:02\",message:\"Index rebuild 40% complete, ETA ~5 minutes\",actor:\"archivist\"}],actions:$R[215]=[],acknowledged:!0,escalated:!0,lastActivity:\"2026-05-12 09:14\"},$R[216]={id:\"INC-003\",title:\"WD MyCloud SMB mount permissions broke backups\",severity:\"P2\",status:\"RESOLVED\",owner:\"lifesupport\",opened:\"2026-05-11 14:30\",resolved:\"2026-05-12 08:22\",summary:\"The WD MyCloud SMB share was mounted as read-only for the openclaw-agent account, preventing all backup scripts from running. The backup folder structure existed on the share but was completely empty.\",tags:$R[217]=[\"backup\",\"wd-mycloud\",\"permissions\",\"smb\"],timeline:$R[218]=[$R[219]={ts:\"14:30\",message:\"Backup script failed: permission denied writing to /Volumes/WD-MyCloud/OpenClaw/logs/\",actor:\"lifesupport\"},$R[220]={ts:\"14:35\",message:\"Investigated mount permissions — volume owned by root:wheel, read-only for agent\",actor:\"engineer\"},$R[221]={ts:\"15:00\",message:\"Incident opened, assigned to Life Support for resolution tracking\",actor:\"monkey\"},$R[222]={ts:\"2026-05-12 08:10\",message:\"New SMB share mounted at /Volumes/OpenClaw-WD with full read/write access\",actor:\"monkey\"},$R[223]={ts:\"2026-05-12 08:22\",message:\"First successful backup completed to new mount path\",actor:\"lifesupport\"}],actions:$R[224]=[$R[225]={label:\"Remount share with write access\",description:\"Mount the WD MyCloud SMB share with user credentials for r/w\",status:\"completed\",completedAt:\"08:10\",completedBy:\"monkey\"},$R[226]={label:\"Run first backup\",description:\"Execute full backup 