{"type":"message","id":"062c9946","parentId":"efd5af26","timestamp":"2026-06-01T21:43:23.765Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"The Crew-New integration has four errors. Fix them all:\n\n1. SYNTAXERROR IN STATIONROOM — \"The string did not match the expected \n   pattern.\" This is the critical one. It's crashing EVERY StationRoom \n   component on the Dashboard. The Replit canvas code is passing a value \n   to a canvas API that doesn't match the expected format — likely an \n   accent colour string or a hex value. Find every canvas draw call in \n   StationRoom.tsx, RoomCanvas.tsx, and crew-sprites.ts that parses or \n   uses colour/accent values. Convert to valid HSL or hex before passing \n   to canvas.\n\n2. EMOJI 404s — 🐒, 🥷, 🔧, 📚 are being used as image src URLs. \n   These are the old emoji fallbacks from when PNG sprites were removed. \n   Now that we have canvas sprites, these should NEVER be used as <img> \n   src. Find where emoji characters are passed as image URLs and either:\n   - Remove the <img> tag entirely (use CrewSprite canvas instead)\n   - Or fix the fallback to not use emoji as a URL\n\n3. HYDRATION MISMATCH — \"16 May at 02:30\" vs \"16 May, 02:30\" on the \n   Tasks page. The date formatter is producing different output on \n   server vs client. Fix the date formatting to be consistent. Use \n   a locale-independent format or suppress during SSR.\n\n4. DUPLICATE KEYS — \"err-err-7e2c02bf-...\" and \"task-done-err-err-...\" \n   are back. This was fixed before but the Replit integration may have \n   reintroduced it. Check useCronData.ts and tasks.tsx for the old \n   `err-${j.id}` pattern that causes the double-prefix collision.\n\nPriority: #1 first (crashes the entire Agent Office), then #2 (broken \nimages), then #3 (hydration), then #4 (console spam).","timestamp":1780350174917,"idempotencyKey":"934df3d9-bd89-4c24-90e4-4edf058493e8:user"}}
