{"type":"message","id":"0f7d5634","parentId":"4c92b7dc","timestamp":"2026-06-01T21:48:04.524Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"But wait — the `oklchToHex` function uses `document.createElement(\"canvas\")` which SSR can't handle. And the `useMemo` with `typeof window !== \"undefined\"` check also creates a hydration issue if the SSR value differs from the client value. A better approach: keep the radar canvas `null` during SSR, render it only client-side in the useEffect. Let me simplify — just guard the canvas draw call:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ca375953-6483-4f5d-9753-3b388dda1ec3","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/StationRoom.tsx","edits":[{"oldText":"  // Pre-compute hex color for canvas API (runs client-side only)\n  const accentHex = useMemo(() => typeof window !== \"undefined\" ? oklchToHex(accent) : \"#6030c0\", [accent]);","newText":"  // Pre-compute hex color for canvas API (client-side only — canvas doesn't exist during SSR)\n  const accentHex = useMemo(() => {\n    try {\n      const c = document.createElement(\"canvas\");\n      c.width = c.height = 1;\n      const ctx2d = c.getContext(\"2d\")!;\n      ctx2d.fillStyle = accent;\n      ctx2d.fillRect(0, 0, 1, 1);\n      const [r, g, b] = ctx2d.getImageData(0, 0, 1, 1).data;\n      return \"#\" + [r, g, b].map(v => v.toString(16).padStart(2, \"0\")).join(\"\");\n    } catch { return \"#6030c0\"; }\n  }, [accent]);"},{"oldText":"    const canvas = canvasRef.current; if (!canvas) return;\n    const ctx = canvas.getContext(\"2d\"); if (!ctx) return;","newText":"    const canvas = canvasRef.current; if (!canvas || typeof window === \"undefined\") return;\n    const ctx = canvas.getContext(\"2d\"); if (!ctx) return;"}]},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/StationRoom.tsx\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"  // Pre-compute hex colo