{"type":"message","id":"8866c8e1","parentId":"25b2ca3d","timestamp":"2026-06-01T21:54:02.521Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The hydration mismatch on line 708: `toLocaleDateString(\"en-GB\", { day: \"numeric\", month: \"short\" })` — on the server (UTC), `new Date(\"2026-05-15T02:30:00.000Z\")` gives \"15 May\", but on the client (BST, UTC+1) the same timestamp gives \"15 May\" too... actually the issue is at line 336 and 648 where `toLocaleString` includes the hour — the UTC server renders `02:30` but the BST client renders `03:30` (or vice versa depending on DST).\n\nLet me look at the exact formatting:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"238cdf9c-de9f-4af1-b257-950c1c9059ae","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":15,"offset":700,"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/routes/tasks.tsx"},"partialArgs":"{\"limit\": 15, \"offset\": 700, \"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/routes/tasks.tsx\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":114356,"output":219,"cacheRead":48128,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":162703,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780350826186,"responseId":"gen-1780350826-UP0lChUhwEmElIq9B921"}}
{"type":"message","id":"c06bded5","parentId":"8866c8e1","timestamp":"2026-06-01T21:54:02.545Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"238cdf9c-de9f-4af1-b257-950c1c9059ae","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"function getTimeAgo(ts: string): string {\n  if (ts === \"just now\") return \"just now\";\n  const d = new Date(ts);\n  const now = new Date();\n  const diff = now.getTime() - d.getTime();\n  if (diff < 60000) return \"just now\";\n  if (diff < 3600000) return `${Math.floor(diff / 60000)}m ago`;\n  if (diff < 86400000) return `${Math.floor(diff / 3600000)}h ago`;\n  return d.toLocaleDateString(\"en-GB\", { day: \"numeric\", month: \"short\" });\n}\n\nfunction calculateProgress(t: Task): number {\n  // Use explicit progress value if set by agent\n  if (t.progress !== undefined) return Math.min(100, Math.max(0, t.progress));\n  // If we have real activity data, derive progress from step completion\n\n[292 more lines in file. Use offset=715 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1780350842544}}
{"type":"message","id":"2b1b420a","parentId":"c06bded5","timestamp":"2026-06-01T21:54:22.730Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The `getTimeAgo` function at line 708 uses `toLocaleDateString(\"en-GB\", { day: \"numeric\", month: \"short\" })`. The server runs in UTC so `new Date(\"2026-05-15T02:30:00.000Z\").toLocaleDateString(\"en-GB\", ...)` gives \"15 May\". On the client in BST (UTC+1), the same call also gives \"15 May\" since 02:30 UTC = 03:30 BST, still the same day. \n\nBut the real mismatch is likely in the `toLocaleString` calls at lines 336 and 648 which include time. Let me look closer at the error message: \"16 May at 02:30\" vs \"16 May, 02:30\". The difference is \"at\" vs \",\" — that's a locale formatting difference. \n\nWait, actually the issue might be in the `TaskCard` component where dates are displayed. Let me look at what exactly is rendering differently:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"1072ecb5-5133-40aa-a22c-c9075fab2707","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":15,"offset":330,"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/routes/tasks.tsx"},"partialArgs":"{\"limit\": 15, \"offset\": 330, \"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/routes/tasks.tsx\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":114704,"output":295,"cacheRead":47872,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":162871,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780350842561,"responseId":"gen-1780350842-UEkaxRl5P7Hwu1oat8RZ"}}
