{"type":"message","id":"1bf275d3","parentId":"2b981d93","timestamp":"2026-06-01T21:56:15.637Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"There it is — the cron error IDs in the data already have the `err-` prefix (e.g., `err-cd8044dc-...`). When `useCronData.ts` does `cron-err-${j.id}`, it produces `cron-err-err-cd8044dc-...`. And the duplicate key issue from before was `err-err-7e2c02bf-...` which comes from the legacy key lookup `err-${j.id}` → `err-err-7e2c02bf-...`.\n\nThe fix: strip the `err-` prefix from `j.id` before constructing the new key, or just use a clean ID format:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"3be48ef3-90e6-499d-a9ba-bfbfe3b6e0d6","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":25,"offset":50,"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/scheduler/useCronData.ts"},"partialArgs":"{\"limit\": 25, \"offset\": 50, \"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/scheduler/useCronData.ts\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":116958,"output":206,"cacheRead":47232,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":164396,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780350958287,"responseId":"gen-1780350958-lx4yeDWoBMR438kK7oPI"}}
{"type":"message","id":"23218cc9","parentId":"1bf275d3","timestamp":"2026-06-01T21:56:15.662Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"3be48ef3-90e6-499d-a9ba-bfbfe3b6e0d6","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"          (savedErrors as Record<string, unknown>[]).map((e) => [e.id, e.status as CronError[\"status\"]])\n        );\n\n        // Extract errors from jobs, merge with saved statuses\n        // Use job ID directly as the error key (deduped by construction since we filter\n        // unique jobs). Prefix with \"cron-err-\" to avoid collisions with other entities.\n        const errorItems: CronError[] = cronJobs\n          .filter((j) => (j.consecutiveErrors ?? 0) > 0 || j.status === \"error\")\n          .map((j) => {\n            const id = `cron-err-${j.id}`;\n            const savedStatus = savedMap.get(id) || savedMap.get(`err-${j.id}`); // also check legacy key\n            // Determine the effective status:\n            // - If job is still failing AND was previously investigated → keep in_progress\n            // - If job is still failing AND was resolved/skipped → the fix didn't work,\n            //   show as \"new\" again (re-escalate)\n            // - If job is still failing with no saved status → show as \"new\"\n            let status: CronError[\"status\"] = \"new\";\n            if (savedStatus === \"in_progress\") {\n              status = \"in_progress\"; // preserve investigation state\n            }\n            // Note: completed/skipped are intentionally NOT preserved here.\n            // If the job fails again after being resolved, it shows as a new error.\n            // This is the correct behavior — the previous resolution didn't fix it.\n            return {\n              id,\n\n[153 more lines in file. Use offset=75 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1780350975661}}
{"type":"message","id":"8e78f8b7","parentId":"23218cc9","timestamp":"2026-06-01T21:56:32.955Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The fix is to strip the `err-` prefix from `j.id` before constructing the composite key. This prevents `cron-err-err-...` and also prevents the legacy `err-${j.id}` lookup from matching incorrectly:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"1e1a4781-4d27-4284-abe4-df050d40bbdd","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/scheduler/useCronData.ts","edits":[{"oldText":"            const id = `cron-err-${j.id}`;\n            const savedStatus = savedMap.get(id) || savedMap.get(`err-${j.id}`); // also check legacy key","newText":"            // Strip legacy \"err-\" prefix from j.id to avoid double-prefix (cron-err-err-...)\n            const cleanId = j.id.replace(/^err-/, \"\");\n            const id = `cron-err-${cleanId}`;\n            const savedStatus = savedMap.get(id) || savedMap.get(`err-${cleanId}`); // also check legacy key"}]},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/scheduler/useCronData.ts\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"            const id = `cron-err-${j.id}`;\\n            const savedStatus = savedMap.get(id) || savedMap.get(`err-${j.id}`); // also check legacy key\", \"newText\": \"            // Strip legacy \\\"err-\\\" prefix from j.id to avoid double-prefix (cron-err-err-...)\\n            const cleanId = j.id.replace(/^err-/, \\\"\\\");\\n            const id = `cron-err-${cleanId}`;\\n            const savedStatus = savedMap.get(id) || savedMap.get(`err-${cleanId}`); // also check legacy key\"}]}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":117460,"output":226,"cacheRead":46848,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":164534,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason"