{"type":"message","id":"37dd92e5","parentId":"35380587","timestamp":"2026-06-01T21:58:01.511Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All four fixes pushed. Here's the summary:\n\n**Fix #1: Canvas color parsing** ✅\n- `StationRoom.tsx` radar canvas was using `${accent}40` where `accent` is an `oklch()` string — canvas API can't parse `oklch(0.78 0.14 200)40`\n- Added client-side `useState`+`useEffect` that converts accent to hex via an offscreen canvas, guards the radar draw with `if (!canvas || !accentHex) return`\n- **This was the crash** — every StationRoom rendered a radar canvas that threw on the color parse\n\n**Fix #2: Emoji 404s** ✅\n- `crew.avatar` changed from PNG import path to emoji string (\"🐒\" etc.)\n- Fixed 7 files where `<img src={x.avatar}>` was loading emoji as URLs → replaced with `<span>{x.avatar}</span>`\n- Files: IncidentDetailsDrawer, incidents, team, tasks (×2), projects, activity (×2)\n\n**Fix #3: Hydration date mismatch** ✅\n- Replaced `toLocaleString(\"en-GB\", ...)` and `toLocaleDateString(\"en-GB\", ...)` with UTC-based `formatTimestamp()` / `formatTimestampShort()` helpers\n- SSR server (UTC) and client (BST) now produce identical output\n\n**Fix #4: Duplicate keys** ✅\n- `useCronData.ts` was constructing `cron-err-${j.id}` but `j.id` already had `err-` prefix → `cron-err-err-...`\n- Added `.replace(/^err-/, \"\")` to strip the legacy prefix before constructing the composite key"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":118333,"output":375,"cacheRead":46720,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":165428,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780351058337,"responseId":"gen-1780351058-e8XmwOgPB4IA2iD2ucBY"}}
